# 📜 Certificate Blockchain System – Smart Contract Setup Guide

This guide explains how to install, configure, compile, and deploy the Smart Contract for the Certificate Blockchain System using **Hardhat**.

---

## 🚀 Prerequisites

Make sure the following software is installed on your system:

| Tool    | Version Required              |
| ------- | ----------------------------- |
| Node.js | v16 / v18 / v20 (Recommended) |
| npm     | Latest                        |
| Git     | Installed                     |
| Hardhat | v2.22.2                       |

⚠️ **Note:** Hardhat v2 does NOT support Node.js v22.
If using Node 22, please switch to Node 18 using NVM.

---

## 🛠️ Project Structure

```
certificate-system/
 ├── backend/
 └── blockchain/
      ├── contracts/
      │    └── Certificate.sol
      ├── scripts/
      │    └── deploy.js
      ├── artifacts/
      ├── hardhat.config.cjs
      └── package.json
```

---

## 📦 Installation Steps

Navigate to blockchain folder:

```bash
cd certificate-system/blockchain
```

---

### 🔹 Initialize Node Project

```bash
npm init -y
```

---

### 🔹 Install Hardhat v2 (Stable)

```bash
npm install --save-dev hardhat@2.22.2
```

---

### 🔹 Install Ethers Plugin

```bash
npm install --save-dev @nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers ethers@5
```

---

## ⚙️ Hardhat Configuration

Create file:

```
hardhat.config.cjs
```

Paste the following:

```js
require("@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers");

module.exports = {
  solidity: "0.8.20",
  networks: {
    localhost: {
      url: "http://127.0.0.1:8545"
    }
  }
};
```

---

## 📄 Smart Contract

Place your contract file inside:

```
contracts/Certificate.sol
```

Example:

```solidity
contract CertificateContract {
    struct Certificate {
        string studentName;
        string courseName;
        string issueDate;
        string certificateHash;
        bool isValid;
    }
}
```

---

## 🧱 Compile Smart Contract

Run:

```bash
npx hardhat compile
```

After successful compilation, ABI will be generated at:

```
artifacts/contracts/Certificate.sol/CertificateContract.json
```

---

## 🛰️ Start Local Blockchain Network

Run the following command in a terminal:

```bash
npx hardhat node
```

This will start a local Ethereum network at:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8545
```

⚠️ Keep this terminal running.

---

## 🚀 Deploy Smart Contract

Create file:

```
scripts/deploy.js
```

Paste:

```js
const hre = require("hardhat");

async function main() {
  const Certificate = await hre.ethers.getContractFactory("CertificateContract");
  const certificate = await Certificate.deploy();

  await certificate.deployed();

  console.log("Certificate deployed to:", certificate.address);
}

main().catch((error) => {
  console.error(error);
  process.exitCode = 1;
});
```

---

### Deploy Command

Open a new terminal and run:

```bash
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network localhost
```

Output:

```
Certificate deployed to: 0xABC123....
```

Copy the deployed contract address.

---

## 🔗 Connect with Backend

### Copy ABI file:

```
blockchain/artifacts/contracts/Certificate.sol/CertificateContract.json
```

Paste into:

```
backend/contracts/Certificate.json
```

---

### Update Backend `.env`

```env
CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0xDEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS
ETHEREUM_NODE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545
```

---

## ▶️ Run Backend Server

Navigate to backend folder:

```bash
cd ../backend
node server.js
```

---

## ✅ Smart Contract is now connected with Backend

You can now:

* Issue Certificates
* Validate Certificates
* Store Certificate Hash on Blockchain
* Verify Certificate Authenticity

---

## 🧾 Important Notes

* Do NOT stop Hardhat node while backend is running.
* Always redeploy contract after restarting Hardhat node.
* Update CONTRACT_ADDRESS in `.env` after every redeployment.

---

## 🛠️ Troubleshooting

| Issue              | Solution                         |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------- |
| Artifact not found | Run `npx hardhat compile`        |
| Invalid Address    | Check CONTRACT_ADDRESS in `.env` |
| Connection Refused | Ensure Hardhat node is running   |

---

🎉 You have successfully set up Blockchain for Certificate System!
